# SQL Server Stored Procedures

## English

This project contains Stored Procedure studies developed using the **Northwind** sample database on Microsoft SQL Server.

The purpose is to apply common data querying and reporting scenarios in business processes using T-SQL and Stored Procedure structures.

## Contents

This project includes the following Stored Procedure examples:

- Listing product information
- Parameterized product search
- Listing products by category
- Displaying order details
- Listing top-selling products
- Listing out-of-stock products
- Finding the customer with the highest number of orders
- Listing customer order history
- Calculating product counts by category
- Calculating average order delivery time

## Technologies Used

- Microsoft SQL Server
- T-SQL
- Northwind Database

## Skills Gained

This project includes practical experience with the following SQL concepts:

- Creating and modifying Stored Procedures
- Using parameters
- INNER JOIN
- GROUP BY
- Aggregate functions (COUNT, SUM, AVG)
- TOP and ORDER BY
- DATEDIFF function
- Data filtering (WHERE)

## Purpose

This repository was created to document my SQL Server and T-SQL application studies and development process.

